Rules
-Everyone should create their own character to do this with
-To do an attack flip a coin (tails is a hit) then roll (depends on weapon) for Damage
-Everyone starts with an inventory space of 7
-depending on the enemy they'll have more or less life eg.
...ant: whereas..soldier(armored):
-To revive you'll have to have to have an ally fight a gauntlet of ten enemies...each with varying life amounts over eight.
-For each point of life an enemy has you gain 5XP
-The first five members who join will become game masters and create the challenges

Might as well write down your info and story on a word page as not to forget stuff.



Scavenging Rolls (Basic, non event)
-1: 3 spheres of glass
-2: (*Same as 17*)
-3-7: Nothing
-8: 25 gold coins
-9: (*Same as 17*)
-10: A new weapon (roll 1-4) Gun, Sword, Stick, Stave
-11: (*Same as 17*)
-12: You lose 3HP from a bear trap
-13: A diamond (sells for 250 gold coins)
-14: You lose 2 life from a large fall
-15: (*Same as 17*)
-16: You meet up with a magic scroll (abilty: Quick Time; Always go first in a battle
-17:Enemy: (roll 1-4) Spider 4HP, Bandit 7, Kobold Sentinal 5,Light Gunner 4.5
-18: You find a runic enchantment (+ 1 to any weapon)
-19-20: You discover a maximum life canister (+1 to max life)




Human 5 HP 5 MP engineer class

Elven 4 HP 7 MP Ranger Class

Kobold 7 HP 3 MP Builder Class

Nodachi 6 HP 4 MP Assassin Class

Lycan 8 HP 2 MP Shapeshifter Class

Dwarven 7 HP 5 MP Smith Class


You gain 1HP and 1MP each level
You must also roll for race picks

A recap of what happened up to now:

The Dark Age (when everything was being established): (page 12-50)
Miner, Andre, dragon and Afterwind found themselves waking up in an empty room, with just a penknife and 10 Arions each. They proceeded to loot everything and kill everything in sight, while being randomly teleported everywhere due to system inconsistencies. During that period, Miner fell asleep in dragon's inventory (don't ask me how) for some time but woke up later on. More random NPCs were slain and the protagonists didn't care how OP they were by looting permanent upgrades after every battle.

The Start of the Journey: (page 50-75)
Miner and Andre suddenly found themselves in jail without their weapons and spells. After getting the key (I wonder why it's so easy) and killing a guard, they rescued an assassin called Ceril Lightshot (that's me XD), who got out of the cell with 2 iron chestplates, a basic penknife and the old pistol given by Andre. He then decided to murder a rat in the jail corridors with perfect accuracy, without knowing that his luck would soon drop into the void.

Ceril followed Miner and Andre for a short time, until the latter two dropped into a hole on the ground and Ceril had a sudden urge to flee from the scene. Andre proceeded down a passage fighting underground monsters. Miner got a leather pouch from a mysterious man (the pouch was later found out to have nothing inside, indicating the man's a troll). They got into a room and killed a gorgon, whose still functional head was cut off by Andre and was later sold to a weird collector for 41 Arions.

dragonice went on to kill some monsters in a gauntlet, and Afterwind just disappeared.

Meanwhile, Ceril acquired more armour, ran out of the prison, murdered more rats, and found himself in front of a strange wooden door on a cliff, which didn't quite match with the rocky terrain. He went through and bumped into Andre and Miner, who just got out of the Gorgon room. They decided to travel together and went to the town of RavenHoard. They went on separate ways to various shops selling loots and buying combat equipment.

In the town, Miner got a permanent armour point with just 5 Arions; Andre bought some potions; Ceril bought his signature weapon: the Steel Dagger. Some random bandits decided to rob Andre. They failed and were killed by Andre and the sneaky Miner. Ceril hurt his right hand while picking up 3 bullets lying on the floor.

dragonice joined Miner in beating up two men. Miner looted the men's pocket and found the Brawler's Glove which made him the protagonist with the highest attack power. Ceril joined Andre in murdering two pathetic robbers who only got 9 Arions from robbing the biggest bank in the town.

Andre had a weird dream that night where everyone sank into quicksand during one of the adventures. They fell into a room with 3 doors marked with the elements of fire, water and wood. On opening the door, they found themselves in the Tomb of Champions, with a book at the center explaining they were the chosen ones who could seek the power of elements. He then woke up presumably.

The next day Ceril found a shiny crystal orb in the town center. He declared it to be an orb showing their near future, shortly before the three being hypnotized and fell unconscious.

To be continued... (I spent an hour typing this up lol)

45424

Note on boosts:
The order of application of boosts is multiplication -> addition -> subtraction. The result is always rounded down.

e.g. If you have a 1.5x damage boost, a +100% damage boost, a +2 damage boost and your opponent has 5 armour, when you roll a 3 for the attack damage, it will deal 3 x (1.5+100%) + 2 - 5 = 4.5 rounded down to 4 damage to the opponent.
